{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause outlines the responsibilities of COMPANY in supporting Bravatek, but lacks clarity on financial contributions and potential liabilities.",
  "operative_text": "COMPANY agrees to use its best efforts to promote and support project lead finding and after-sales support of Bravatek by: a. Listing Bravatek in all appropriate sales and marketing materials as a non-exclusive alliance partner (with focus of government customers)   b. Provide timely responses to both technical and administrative questions posed by Bravatek.   c. Promote Bravatek's product and service offerings whenever possible.   d. Aid Bravatek in the writing of any technical/marketing/sales documents when requested and participate in mutually-agreed upon sales calls.   e. Provide Bravatek with co-branded marketing material that can be emailed or handed to prospective clients.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity on the financial contributions of COMPANY to support Bravatek, particularly regarding potential liabilities for Bravatek's operations and performance.",
      "severity": "minor",
      "references": ["COMPANY"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "non-operator" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause outlines the joint and several liability of Bravatek and COMPANY in the joint venture, which could lead to financial disputes if not properly managed.",
  "operative_text": "Bravatek and COMPANY agree to jointly develop and implement a joint Product Solution and Application Strategy whereby targeted markets/potential client- types/applications are mutually agreed upon; support each other in all agreed-upon technical, marketing and promotional efforts; develop a joint strategy for developing new product/services/capabilities to mutually benefit both parties; utilize each other as Preferred Vendors for services whenever possible upon mutual agreement.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "Joint and several liability is not explicitly defined. This could lead to financial disputes if the parties disagree on responsibility for costs or obligations.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["Bravatek", "COMPANY"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause lacks clarity on the mechanics for capital calls, including how shortfalls are handled and what constitutes 'necessary and expected costs'. This raises concerns about potential dilution of ownership and financial risks.",
  "operative_text": "When custom Products are designed, developed and to be delivered to Bravatek-identified perspective clients, the parties shall agree to a proposed sales price for use during the project in writing prior to the commencement of each project. For any Product or Solution sold to any perspective clients introduced by Bravatek registered with COMPANY via email to COMPANY's CEO and delivered through Bravatek or a COMPANY-designated distribution affiliate(s) or sales channel(s), Bravatek will receive a lead-finder fee, to be mutually discussed and finally decided by COMPANY at the range of minimum of 10% to maximum of 20% of project revenue, with an exact fee to be depending upon the overall project sales margin and cost of development and delivery of each project, payable NET 30 days after each client payment on delivered products received at COMPANY's bank account.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity on how capital calls will be made and the mechanics for funding shortfalls. This raises concerns about potential dilution of ownership and financial risks.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["project revenue", "capital calls", "funding shortfalls"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "non-operator" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause defines 'Confidential Information' and outlines non-disclosure obligations for the parties involved in the joint venture. It lacks clarity on how to handle information that becomes publicly available or is disclosed by a third party, potentially leading to disputes.",
  "operative_text": "‘Confidential Information’ shall mean any and all technical and non-technical information, documents and materials related to client projects of party and products, services and business of each of the parties. COMPANY and Bravatek agree to maintain in strict confidence and not to disclose or disseminate, or to use for any purposes other than performance of the projects, the Confidential Information disclosed. The obligation of non-disclosure shall not apply to the following:   a. Information at or after such time that is publicly available through no fault of either party   b. Information at or after such time that is disclosed to either party by a third party entitled to disclose such information   c. Information which is required by law to be disclosed to federal, state or local authorities.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity on how to handle information that becomes publicly available or is disclosed by a third party, potentially leading to disputes.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["clause 5"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause defines confidentiality obligations for a period after termination, but lacks specifics on what constitutes 'information' or how it will be enforced.",
  "operative_text": "For a period of five (5) years after termination of this Agreement, the parties shall treat as confidential all information and take every reasonable precaution and use all reasonable efforts to prevent the unauthorized disclosure of the same. The parties agree to take all steps reasonably necessary and appropriate to ensure that their employees, agents, and/or assistants treat all information as confidential and to ensure that such employees, agents, and/or assistants are familiar with and abide by the terms of this Agreement.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity on what constitutes 'information' and how it will be enforced. This could lead to ambiguity and potential disputes regarding confidentiality obligations.",
      "severity": "minor",
      "references": ["5 years", "parties", "employees", "agents", "assistants"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause outlines a standard twelve-month term with automatic renewal, but also provides for termination by either party upon ninety (90) days' notice.",
  "operative_text": "The term of this Agreement is twelve (12) months from the date hereof, and will be automatically renewed for one (1) additional twelve month period unless either party shall notify the other in writing of its intention not to renew. Such notice must be given ninety (90) days prior to expiration of the original term. This Agreement may also be terminated by either party upon ninety (90) days written notice.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The agreement lacks clarity on how capital contributions are handled and what constitutes 'necessary and expected costs' without further definition.",
      "severity": "info",
      "references": ["capital contributions"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "The clause lacks clarity on how capital contributions are handled, what constitutes 'necessary and expected costs', and the mechanics for funding shortfalls. This raises concerns about potential dilution of ownership and financial risks.",
  "operative_text": "Any notices required under this Agreement shall be delivered to:   Bravatek Technologies, Inc. 2028 E. Ben White Blvd., Unit #240-2835 Austin, Texas 78741   Sibannac, Inc. 2122 E Highland Avenue, STE 425 Phoenix, AZ 85016\nThis Agreement is entered into in the State of Texas and shall be interpreted according to the laws of the State of Texas.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause lacks clarity on how capital contributions are handled, what constitutes 'necessary and expected costs' without further definition. This raises concerns about potential dilution of ownership and financial risks.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["clause 8"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause outlines indemnification responsibilities for both parties in the joint venture, potentially exposing either party to significant financial risk if claims arise.",
  "operative_text": "Indemnification   COMPANY shall indemnify Bravatek, its directors, officers and employees, for any and all damages, costs, expenses, and other liabilities, including reasonable attorney's fees and court costs incurred in connection with any third-party claim, action or proceeding arising from the negligence or intentional misconduct of COMPANY or breach of COMPANY of any of its obligations under this Agreement.   Bravatek shall indemnify COMPANY, its directors, officers and employees, for any and all damages, costs, expenses, and other liabilities, including reasonable attorney's fees and court costs, incurred in connection with any third-party claim, action or proceeding arising from the negligence or intentional misconduct of Bravatek or breach of Bravatek of any of its obligations under this Agreement.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "This clause outlines indemnification responsibilities for both parties. However, it lacks clarity on the scope and limitations of such indemnities. This could lead to significant financial exposure for either party in case of claims arising from negligence or intentional misconduct.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["COMPANY", "Bravatek"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause limits modification to written agreements, potentially hindering flexibility during unforeseen circumstances or operational changes.",
  "operative_text": "No changes or modifications of this Agreement or any of its terms shall be deemed effective unless in writing and executed by the parties hereto.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "This clause limits modification to written agreements, potentially hindering flexibility during unforeseen circumstances or operational changes.",
      "severity": "minor",
      "references": ["clause 11"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause restricts assignment of the entire agreement, potentially hindering flexibility and limiting Acme Holdings' ability to transfer its interest in the joint venture.",
  "operative_text": "This Agreement shall not be assignable by either party without the prior written consent of the other party.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "The clause restricts assignment of the entire agreement, potentially hindering flexibility and limiting Acme Holdings' ability to transfer its interest in the joint venture.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["This Agreement"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "operator" 
}

{
  "clauseRiskSummary": "This clause asserts the complete agreement's scope and supersedes all prior agreements, but it doesn't address specific risk mitigation or liability provisions.",
  "operative_text": "This Agreement represents the complete and entire understanding between the parties regarding the subject matter hereof and supersedes all prior negotiations, representations, or agreements, either written or oral, regarding this subject matter. This Agreement shall not be considered accepted, approved or otherwise effective until signed by the appropriate parties.",
  "concerns": [
    {
      "text": "This clause lacks specific provisions for risk mitigation, such as liability caps or indemnification clauses, which could leave the non-operator exposed to significant financial risks.",
      "severity": "major",
      "references": ["entire agreement"]
    }
  ],
  "favoursWhom": "neutral"
}

